    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_fælvaryn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fælvaryn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>fælværd</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fælvarun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>fælvard</orth></form></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>пробовать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>try</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>испытывать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>test</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>bafælvarūt ma he ūcy xorz mīnīwæg</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>испытайте-ка это хорошее свойство</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>try this good feature</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"
                            /><biblScope>102</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>dæ cirq... yscyrǧ kæn æmæ jæ bafælvar mæ bærzæjyl</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>наточи свой меч и испытай его на моей шее</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>sharpen your sword and test it on my neck</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Нарт._сказ."
                            /><biblScope>87</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Из %ifæl-war-%i ← <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*pari-var-</w></mentioned>. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>var-</w>
                        <gloss><q>выбирать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>var-</w>
                        <gloss><q>выбирать (для себя)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>предпочитать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">велѣти</w>, <w n="0">волꙗ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"><lang/>
                        <w>waljan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>wählen</w>
                        <gloss><q>выбирать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                            ><w>wollen</w>
                        <gloss><q>хотеть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>volo</w>
                        <gloss><q>хочу</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр. Глагол %ivar-%i означал также
                    (например в ведийском) <mentioned xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><lang/>
                        <w/>
                        <gloss><q>предоставлять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>доставлять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>давать</q></gloss></mentioned>. Это значение удержалось в <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_waryn"/> | %ii-warun%i ‘распределять’, ‘делить’.
                    Ср. также <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævzaryn"/> ‘выбирать’ и <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_bar"/> ‘воля’, ‘право’.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">From %ifæl-war-%i ← <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*pari-var-</w></mentioned>. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>var-</w>
                        <gloss><q>choose</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>var-</w>
                        <gloss><q>choose (for oneself)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>prefer</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>velěti</w>, <w>volʲa</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"><lang/>
                        <w>waljan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>wählen</w>
                        <gloss><q>choose</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                            ><w>wollen</w>
                        <gloss><q>want</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>volo</w>
                        <gloss><q>I want</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. The verb %ivar-%i also meant
                    (e.g., in Vedic) <mentioned xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><lang/>
                        <w/>
                        <gloss><q>give</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>deliver</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>yield</q></gloss></mentioned>. This meaning is present in <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_waryn"/> | %ii-warun%i ‘distribute’, ‘share’. Cf.
                    also <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævzaryn"/> ‘choose’ and <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_bar"/> ‘will’, ‘right’.</etym>
            </entry>
